# merge sort
## my goal with this project
to learn how the merge sort worked, and how to implement it myself in c++
## what i learned
merge sort works by recursively splitting a vector in half until each piece has one element. then merges the pieces back together in sorted order.
the merge works by maintaining an iterator in each half and emplacing and advancing the iterator with the lower value, then appending the remainder of the other iterator once one is at the end.
both odd and even sized vectors work due to how integer division is handled.
## challenges i came across
initially i used raw pointers for iterators. this wouldn't have worked.
i also was comparing to nullptr, but corrected myself and compared to .end(), as that is how you properly evaluate vector iterators.
forgot the edge case in the recursive function. i thought this would be handled itself, but it was needed.
tried to return by reference, but the vector is not sorted in place so that would not work either.
## what i would do differently next time
think about return type harder. think about ownership harder.
implement the base case first, then write the recursive logic.
